Functional Requirements:
2.1. Administrators should have the ability to define permissions, restrictions, and acceess rights for each user role in the system.
2.2. Users should be able to select a profile/role and be granted access based on their assigned roles to prevent access to unauthorized access to sensitive information or functionalities.
2.3. Administrators should have the capability to temporarily suspend or permanently revoke access privileges for user roles, ensuring compliance and security.
2.4. Administrators should be able to search for users using certain filters like role to make finding and retreiving information of user easier.
